sentences: His father, Jim Moloney, was a Hollywood screenwriter who died in 1994.
Moloney joined Creative Artists Agency (CAA) as an intern in June 1983 while attending USC.
Due to an addiction to cocaine that started in 1995, Moloney was unable to perform on the job, and was later forced out of CAA.
In 1999, he joined Paradise Music & Entertainment, but his contract was terminated due to his frequent absences.
He committed suicide by hanging himself two days after he turned 35 on November 16, 1999.
